programme.title: Ipswich Town vs Liverpool (MW01)
programme.desc: Ipswich Town's most recent Premier League game was in May 2002 against Liverpool at Anfield, losing 5-0 as they were relegated. Since then, the two sides have only faced once, a 1-1 draw in the League Cup in December 2002 before the Tractor Boys lost 5-4 on penalties.

programme.title: Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Chelsea (MW02)
programme.desc: Chelsea are winless in four away league games against Wolves (D1 L3), since a 5-2 victory in September 2019 under Frank Lampard.

programme.title: Everton vs AFC Bournemouth (MW03)
programme.desc: Everton have lost all five of their Premier League games in August under Sean Dyche without scoring a single goal. Indeed, Dyche has a win ratio of just 12.5% in August, the worst percentage of any manager to manage more than 10 games in August.

programme.title: Tottenham Hotspur v Arsenal (MW04)
programme.desc: Arsenal have won their last two Premier League away games against Tottenham, as many as in their previous 17 such visits (D6 L9). They last won three consecutive away north London derbies between January 1987 and September 1988.

programme.title: Manchester City vs Arsenal (MW05)
programme.desc: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last nine Premier League home games against Arsenal (W7 D2) since a 2-0 defeat in January 2015.

programme.title: Chelsea vs Brighton and Hove Albion (MW06)
programme.desc: Nicolas Jackson has been involved in 13 goals in his last 13 Premier League games for Chelsea (9 goals, 4 assists), one more than he'd managed in his first 27 appearances (9 goals, 3 assists).

programme.title: Brentford vs Wolverhampton Wanderers (MW07)
programme.desc: Wolves are unbeaten in their last five away league games against Brentford (W3 D2), winning two of their three visits in the Premier League.

programme.title: Southampton vs Leicester City (MW08)
programme.desc: Having done the double over Leicester in their last Premier League campaign together of 2022-23, Southampton lost both Championship meetings with the Foxes last term by an aggregate score of 9-1.

programme.title: Brentford vs Ipswich Town (MW09)
programme.desc: Brentford have lost just one of their last nine league games against Ipswich (W4 D4), with the first meeting between the sides since a 2-0 home win for the Bees in April 2019.

programme.title: Brighton and Hove Albion vs Manchester City (MW11)
programme.desc: Brighton have conceded more Premier League goals against Manchester City than they have against any other opponent (40), failing to keep a clean sheet in any of their 14 such matches.

programme.title: Arsenal vs Liverpool (MW09)
programme.desc: Arsenal have won their last two Premier League home games against Liverpool, last having a longer such run between 2004 and 2006 (4).

programme.title: Manchester City vs Tottenham Hotspur (MW12)
programme.desc: Manchester City have won just three of their last 10 Premier League games against Tottenham (D2 L5) and are looking to win consecutive meetings with them for the first time since April 2019.

programme.title: West Ham United vs Arsenal (MW13)
programme.desc: West Ham have lost more Premier League games overall (36) and at home (15) against Arsenal than they have vs any other opponent in the competition.

programme.title: Manchester United vs Nottingham Forest (MW15)
programme.desc: Following their 2-1 victory in December 2023, Nottingham Forest are looking to win consecutive league games against Manchester United for the first time since April 1992.

programme.title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa (MW10)
programme.desc: Aston Villa have won three of their last four Premier League away games against Tottenham (L1), including the last two in a row under Unai Emery. They last won three consecutive away league games against Spurs between 1922 and 1924.

programme.title: Manchester City vs Manchester United (MW16)
programme.desc: Manchester United have lost each of their last three Premier League away games against Man City, conceding 13 goals in the process. They last lost four consecutive league visits to the Citizens between 1952 and 1955.

programme.title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Chelsea (MW15)
programme.desc: Tottenham have won just one of their last 11 Premier League games against Chelsea (D2 L8), picking up a 2-0 home win in February 2023.

programme.title: Newcastle United vs Liverpool (MW14)
programme.desc: Newcastle have lost their last six Premier League games against Liverpool, and are winless in 15 against the Reds since a 2-0 win in December 2015 (D4 L11).

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
programme.desc: The 1980s begin with Herschel Walker leading Georgia to a national title as a freshman. After Bear Bryant retires in 1982 and passes away four weeks later, control of the SEC is eventually transferred to Pat Dye and Bo Jackson at Auburn.

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
programme.desc: The 1990s bring change, with expansion and the sport's first-ever conference championship game. Florida's Steve Spurrier fashions an era of high-octane offense, and his Gators form a rivalry with Tennessee and QB Peyton Manning.

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
programme.desc: Nick Saban comes to LSU in 2000 and eventually wins the Tigers' first national championship since 1958 - a feat matched by Les Miles. At Florida, Tim Tebow becomes a cult hero and wins two national titles with Urban Meyer's Gators.

programme.title: Saturdays In the South: A History of SEC Football
